folder: Holland Avenue & Arlington Place, Staten Island, NY
text:
138 Holland Avenue, west side, between Arlington Place and Macromac Place, showing the exterior of a frame dwelling. The house does not have a water supply and drinking water is obtained from a pump in the yard. As the dwelling is situated near the Downey Shipbuilding Corporation yard, and is one of a number of similar ones, it is very likely that it is inhabited by the shipyard workers and their families.

About 1910

Committee on Housing
Charity Organization Society

folder: Holland Avenue & Arlington Place, Staten Island, NY
text:
182 Holland Avenue, west side, between Arlington Place and Tufts Place, showing two views of a workers' dwelling. The house, one of a number of similar ones, is situated near the shipyard of the Downey Shipbuilding Corporation and is, in all likelihood, inhabited by the shipyard hands and their families. The sign over the front doorway reads: Nooks and Raseta. Bachmann Lager Beer.

About 1910
